Book of Combos 1.description: An introductory text for first-time combiners. Improves your success rate.

Book of Combos 2.description: A basic text. Owning Book 1 and this improves your combining success rate.

Book of Combos 3.description: An intermediate text. Owning Books 1, 2 and this improves your combining success rate.

Book of Combos 4.description: An advanced text. Owning Books 1-3 and this improves your combining success rate.

Book of Combos 5.description: A pro-level text. Owning Books 1-4 and this improves your combining success rate.

Potion.description: Restores a small amount of Health. Try to combine these into something Mega-better!

Mega Potion.description: Restores a moderate amount of Health. This potion is a hunter's best friend.

Nutrients.description: Very slightly increases your maximum Health level.

Mega Nutrients.description: Slightly increases your maximum Health level.

Antidote.description: Removes all traces of poison from your system.

Immunizer.description: Boosts your natural ability to heal.

Dash Juice.description: Lets you run without tiring for a short period of time.

Mega Dash Juice.description: Lets you run without tiring for longer than with regular Dash Juice.

Demondrug.description: Boosts your Attack by filling you with -- guess what? -- demonic strength.

Mega Demondrug.description: Boosts your Attack even more than a regular Demondrug.

Might Pill.description: Temporarily endows you with the strength of a mighty god. Potent!

Armorskin.description: Boosts your Defense by turning your skin as hard as rock.

Mega Armorskin.description: Boosts your Defense even more than a regular Armorskin.

Adamant Pill.description: Temporarily makes your skin as hard as adamant. Potent!

Cool Drink.description: Provides temporary relief from extreme heat.

Hot Drink.description: Provides temporary relief from extreme cold.

Cleanser.description: Immediately removes any ice or mud on your body. Clean as a whistle!

Deodorant.description: An item that cures Stench. Releases a puff of deoderizing smoke when thrown down.

Psychoserum.description: Temporarily sharpens your sixth sense and attunes you to the ways of monsters.

Herbal Medicine.description: Removes all traces of poison and restores a slight amount of Health.

Max Potion.description: Fully restores Health and increases your maximum Health level all the way.

Ancient Potion.description: Fully restores Health and Stamina, and raises the max levels of both all the way,

Catalyst.description: Works with other materials to enhance their effects. Cannot be used by itself.

Energy Drink.description: This bottle is all you'll need to wake up! Shakes off sleep and restores Stamina.

Gunpowder.description: A dangerous substance that explodes when struck or heated.

Lifecrystals.description: Mysterious crystals long worshipped as a source of life.

Lifepowder.description: A Lifecrystal combination used as medicine. Heals with a single touch.

Dust of Life.description: A medicine with strone curative properties. Studied in secret, it is said to restore youth.

Tranquilizer.description: Medicine that works as an anesthetic when Combined.

Mystery Charm.description: A modest good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

Shining Charm.description: A curious good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

Timeworn Charm.description: A powerful good-luck charm. What does it do? Finish the Quest and you'll find out.

Powercharm.description: An amulet that raises Attack. Just carrying this gives you demonic strength.

Powertalon.description: A powerful amulet that raises Attack. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

Armorcharm.description: An amulet that raises Defense. Just carrying this hardens your skin like rock.

Armortalon.description: A powerful amulet that raises Defense. Made with a Deviljho Talon.

Raw Meat.description: Meat carved from a monster. Can be cooked, combined, or use to set a trap.

Poisoned Meat.description: Raw Meat that poisons whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Tinged Meat.description: Raw Meat that paralyzes whatever eats it. Makes great bait for traps.

Drugged Meat.description: Raw Meat that puts whatever eats it to sleep. Makes great bait for traps.

Rare Steak.description: Provides a small boost to your Stamina. This one's still red in the middle

Well-done Steak.description: Provides a moderate boost to your Stamina. Meat done right!

Burnt Meat.description: Meat that has been burnt to a crisp. It might boost your Stamina, or it might drain it ..

Chilled Meat.description: Meat that cools the body, wards off heat, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

Hot Meat.description: Meat that warms the body, wards off the cold, and boosts a moderate amount of Stamina.

Boomerang.description: An usually-shaped weapon from abroad that returns to its user when thrown.

Throwing Knife.description: A standard throwing knife. Flies straight and true.

Poison Knife.description: A throwing knife with a venom-coated blade. Poisons targets.

Sleep Knife.description: A throwing knife whose blade has been dusted with sleeping agents.

Paralysis Knife.description: A throwing knife coated with toxins that paralyze a target.

Tranq Knife.description: A throwing knife used for capturing monsters ensnared in traps.

Bomb Casing.description: A base material for making hand-thrown bombs.

Paintball.description: Toss this scented paint at a monster to mark it, allowing you to track its position.

Flash Bomb.description: Flashes brightly on impact. Toss this right under a monster's nose to blind it.

Sonic Bomb.description: A grenade-like item that emits a high frequency blast of sound on detonation.

Dung.description: That's right: monster poop. The odor reveals too much about the monster's diet.

Dung Bomb.description: Releases an odor monsters find repulsive. It may even drive them away... or not.

Smoke Bomb.description: Creates a large cloud of smoke wherever it lands.

Farcaster.description: Instantly transports you back to base camp.

Tranq Bomb.description: A hand grenade used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

Net.description: A sturdy net able to support a certain amount of weight without breaking.

Trap Tool.description: A tool you'll need to put a Pitfall Trap or other traps together with.

Pitfall Trap.description: Activates when something heavy walks across. Use this to capture monsters.

Shock Trap.description: Immobilizes a target. You can use this to capture monsters.

Small Barrel.description: How many whiffs does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

Large Barrel.description: How many licks does it take to find out what was in this empty barrel? Just one!

Barrel Bomb S.description: A small time bomb. You can use it underwater.

Barrel Bomb S+.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb S. Small, but it packs a punch. You can use it underwater.

Barrel Bomb L.description: A potent bomb that detonates on impact. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

Barrel Bomb L+.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L. Deadly. Waterproofed, so it still works underwater.

Bounce Bomb+.description: An improved version of the Bounce Bomb. Requires some skill to use.

Felvine Bomb.description: Emits a scent Felynes love. Try hitting monsters with it.

Huskberry.description: A berry that is hollow on the inside.

Normal S Lv2.description: Non-specialized ammo. More powerful than Lv1.

Normal S Lv3.description: Non-specialized ammo that ricochets, resulting in high damage.

Pierce S Lv1.description: Armor-piercing ammo that deals multiple hits to some monsters.

Pierce S Lv2.description: Armor-piercing ammo. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

Pierce S Lv3.description: Armor-piercing ammo. This highest level deals the most hits.

Pellet S Lv1.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Deals multiple hits at close range.

Pellet S Lv2.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. Higher-level ammo deals additional hits.

Pellet S Lv3.description: Ammo that hits a wide area. This highest level deals the most hits

Crag S Lv1.description: Powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

Crag S Lv2.description: Very powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

Crag S Lv3.description: Extremely powerful ammo that lodges in a target, then explodes.

Clust S Lv1.description: Fragments into three shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

Clust S Lv2.description: Fragments into four shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

Clust S Lv3.description: Fragments into five shells upon impact. Beware of friendly fire!

Flaming S.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Fire.

Water S.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Water.

Thunder S.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Thunder.

Freeze S.description: Ammo that packs extra punch against monsters susceptible to Ice.

Dragon S.description: Mysterious ammo that won't work in regular Bowguns.

Poison S Lv1.description: Ammo dipped in poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

Poison S Lv2.description: Ammo dipped in deadly poison. Some targets require multiple shots.

Para S Lv1.description: Ammo that causes paralysis. Some targets require multiple shots.

Para S Lv2.description: Ammo that paralyzes quickly. Some targets require multiple shots.

Sleep S Lv1.description: Ammo containing a sleeping agent. Some targets require multiple shots.

Sleep S Lv2.description: Ammo packed with sleeping agents. Some targets require multiple shots.

Exhaust S Lv1.description: Special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

Exhaust S Lv2.description: Enhanced special ammo that drains monsters' stamina.

Slicing S.description: Special ammo that ejects sharp blades on impact. Can it sever tails?

WyvernFire.description: Ammo patterned after Wyvern's Fire. Not as potent, but can be rapid-fired.

Recover S Lv1.description: Ammo that restores a small amount of Health to the target.

Recover S Lv2.description: Ammo that restores a moderate amount of Health to the target.

Demon S.description: Ammo that fills the target with savage amounts of strength.

Armor S.description: Ammo that hardens the skin, guarding against attacks and Wind Pressure.

Paint S.description: Ammo that marks a monster's position on your Map for a limited time.

Tranq S.description: Bowgun ammo used to capture monsters ensnared in traps.

Power Coating.description: An arrow coating that increases the Attack of arrows fired. Capacity 50.

C.Range Coating.description: An arrow coating that increases close-range power and melee Sharpness. Capacity 20.

Poison Coating.description: An arrow coating that applies Poison effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

Para Coating.description: An arrow coating that applies Paralysis effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

Sleep Coating.description: An arrow coating that applies Sleep effects to arrows fired. Capacity 20

Exhaust Coating.description: An arrow coating that causes arrows fired to drain monsters' stamina. Capacity 20

Paint Coating.description: An arrow coating that marks a monster's position on the map for a limited time. Capacity 99.

Worm.description: A fishing lure. Wriggles underwater, enticing those fishies to bite.

Mega Fishing Fly.description: A fishing lure. Causes a feeding frenzy. No fish can resist this one!

Frog.description: Know any monsters good at fishing? Try fighting fire with fire.

Sushifish Bait.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Sushifish go, mmm.

Burst Bait.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes fish that rupture upon death go mmm

Goldenfish Bait.description: A fishing lure with chum that makes Goldenfish go, mmm.

Old Pickaxe.description: A cheap pickaxe with an easily nicked blade.

Iron Pickaxe.description: A pickaxe with a reasonably strong blade.

Mega Pickaxe.description: A pickaxe tempered with steel. This one won't nick easily.

Old Bug Net.description: A cheap net for catching bugs. It tears easily.

Bug Net.description: A durable net for catching bugs.

Mega Bug Net.description: An extremely durable net for catching bugs. This one is made to last.

BBQ Spit.description: Just what you need to cook meat. A must-have item for any hungry hunter.

Whetstone.description: A standard-sized Whetstone. Use it to restore a weapon's Sharpness.

Binoculars.description: Allow you to see farther and observe from a distance.

Garbage.description: Junk created when a combination attempt fails.

Field Horn.description: Used to attract certain monsters -- blow at your own risk. May break when used.

Health Horn.description: Restores Health to those who hear it. May break when used.

Antidote Horn.description: Eliminates poison in the blood of those who hear it. May break when used.

Demon Horn.description: Increases the strength of those who hear it. May break when used.

Armor Horn.description: Bolsters the defenses of those who hear it. May break when used.

Honey.description: Full of nutrients, but indigestible in this form.

Herb.description: Restores a very small amount of Health, but the flavor's not too hot.

Antidote Herb.description: A plant used in antidotes. It sometimes cures poison when eaten by itself.

Ivy.description: A vine of tough fibers. Woven, it is sturdy enough to hold a person's weight.

Sap Plant.description: The sap it secretes is a strong adhesive. Careful you don't glue your Pouch shut!

Felvine.description: Melynxes' favorite food -- they just have to steal it.

Gloamgrass Bud.description: A night-blooming flower from a special herb native to Moga. It may have healing properties.

Hot Pepper.description: Blazingly spicy. Sure, it'll warm you up, but it's too hot to handle on its own.

Blue Mushroom.description: A well-known Combo material used to augment power. The deeper the blue, the better.

Nitroshroom.description: A hard-to-find mushroom with the power to generate blazing heat.

Toadstool.description: Logic says not to eat this poisonous fungus, but don't write it off completely.

Exciteshroom.description: This one has a very strange aroma... Edible? Only one way to find out.

Dragon Toadstool.description: A dangerous fungus said to suck the life out of the one who plucks it. Beware.

Paintberry.description: A berry with a shockng hue and an overwhelming scent. Look out: it WILL stain!

Might Seed.description: Temporarily raises your Attack when ingested by improving energy flow.

Adamant Seed.description: Temporarily raises your Defense when ingested by hardening tissue.

Nulberry.description: A mysterious berry that cures all elemental Blights (Fire, Water, Ice, Thunder, and Dragon)

Dragonfell Berry.description: Eat this to cure Dragonblight and temporarily increase Dragon Resistance.

Scatternut.description: A nut that violently ejects its contents when struck.

Needleberry.description: A berry covered with needle-like thorns.

Bomberry.description: A berry that explodes when struck.

Bumblepumpkin.description: A trendy orange pumpkin. If left undisturbed, it can grow to gigantic proportions.

Stone.description: A rock with just the right heft for throwing. Tried and tested!

Iron Ore.description: Ore with high iron content. Can be smelted and forged into various equipment.

Earth Crystal.description: Crystallized microbes which are prized as an abrasive when forging weapons.

Machalite Ore.description: An ore harder than iron, but also several times more difficult to forge with.

Dragonite Ore.description: An ore that yields metal superior to that of Machalite. Rare and valuable.

Lightcrystal.description: An extemely hard substance with a faint glow. Sometimes used for crafting tools.

Ice Crystal.description: Ice that will not melt at room temparatures. Can be used to create denser ore.

Firestone.description: Combusts even at room temperature. Its high heat can be used to fuse materials.

Carbalite Ore.description: An ore still being researched. It yields even better metal than Dragonite.

Fucium Ore.description: An ore composed of a mysterious metal, capable of fusing nearly any two materials together.

Eltalite Ore.description: A promising new ore that produces higher quality metal than Carbalite Ore.

Meldspar Ore.description: An ore composed of a durable, flexible metal that works well as a combining agent.

Firecell Stone.description: A magma-like deposit that only trained hands can properly work with.

Allfire Stone.description: An ore that blazes with an all-consuming flame. Requires considerable skill to mine.

Purecrystal.description: A crystal that's 100% pure. Hard enough to be used in workshop tools.

Armor Stone.description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Combine with other materials to create coating for armor.

Armor Sphere.description: Reacts uniquely to heat. Fuse this to armor to increase its strength.

Armor Sphere+.description: Fuse this high-quality Armor Sphere to existing armor to increase its strength.

Adv Armor Sphere.description: An advanced Armor Sphere. Rare in Moga Village. Save it for that special upgrade.

Whetfish.description: A fish with a dorsal fin hard enough to sharpen weapons with.

Sushifish.description: A fatty, delicious fish that restores a small amount of Health when consumed.

Sleepyfish.description: A fish that contains sleeping agents.

Pin Tuna.description: A fish with jaws covered in tiny, needle-like spikes.

Popfish.description: A fish that literally pops when it dies.

Scatterfish.description: A fish that dashes itself to pieces when it dies.

Burst Arowana.description: A fish that bursts open when it dies

Bomb Arowana.description: A fish that explodes when it dies.

Glutton Tuna.description: A fish that eats anything -- allowing you to sometimes get items from its stomach.

Small Goldenfish.description: A rare fish that commands a high price, but beware its ferocity, rookies!

Wanchovy.description: A fish that can induce exhaustion.

Blue Cutthroat.description: A fish that emits blue light. Its sharp body will cut you to pieces if you're not careful

Insect Husk.description: The remains of an insect. You must be one hardcore collector to hang onto this!

Stinkhopper.description: A grasshopper with a foul odor. Make fishing lures with it；its scent drives explosive fish wild.

Snakebee Larva.description: An unusual larva. Make fishing lures with it； its scent drives Goldenfish wild.

Godbug.description: An insect said to live 1000 years -- but no one's lived long enough to prove it.

Bitterbug.description: Boosts your natural ability to heal when eaten. It also cures poison... sometimes.

Flashbug.description: A nocturnal insect sometimes found in daylight. They emit a bright flash upon death.

Thunderbug.description: Releases an electric shock when struck. Used to light rooms and start fires.

Killer Beetle.description: This insect's hard shell is often used as an abrasive.

Hercudrome.description: Said to be the world's strongest bug. Used in forging, cooking, and more.

Fulgurbug.description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.

Rare Scarab.description: A rare and valuable insect that greatly assists in the bonding of metals.

Emperor Hopper.description: A grasshopper with an exceptionally strong shell. Prized as a crafting material.

Flutterfly.description: A butterfly with shimmering wings. So rarely seen in the wild, many believe it to be a myth.

Butterfly Beetle.description: A strange insect with the large jaws of a beetle and the delicate wings of a butterfly.

Monster Bone S.description: A handy material used to make everything from equipment to sundries.

Monster Bone M.description: A nicely-sized bone. Strong yet flexible, it's as reliable as steel and wood.

Monster Bone L.description: Wyvern bone needed to craft larger items. The right item will fuse this to a shell.

Mystery Bone.description: A weathered bone. Not sturdy enough to use in forging.

Unknown Skull.description: An animal skull worn and weathered beyond identification.

Monster Bone+.description: A top-quality monster bone. Hard to find, but vital for crafting powerful equipment.

Monster Keenbone.description: A rare bone with a razor-sharp tip that retains its strength even when crafted.

Monster Hardbone.description: A precious bone rarely yielded by large wyverns. Difficult to forge, but prized for its strength.

Monster Slogbone.description: An incredibly strong bone harvested from a fearsome wyvern. Its heft is impressive.

Avian Finebone.description: A bone from a Jaggi or other bird wyvern. Small in size, but high in quality.

Avian Stoutbone.description: The robust bone of a bird wyvern. Durable and easy to craft with this.

Jumbo Bone.description: A large, thick bone. Often cut apart in workshops for use in crafting.

Stoutbone.description: The large, sturdy bone of a beast. Prized by blacksmiths as a prime forging material.

Massive Bone.description: An impossibly hard bone from a large beast. It exceeds all known standards for crafting material.

Dragonbone Relic.description: A curiously unfossilized bone from a dragon that once roamed these lands.

Wyvern Fang.description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder shatters them, generating shrapnel.

Wyvern Claw.description: Used in Bowgun bullet points. Gunpowder triggers a blast with a wide radius.

Bird Wyvern Gem.description: A valuable gem that can be harvested from Jaggi and other bird wyverns.

Fey Wyvern Gem.description: An exceptionally pure gem taken from a bird wyvern. Its fragility makes it difficult to carve.

Poison Sac.description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

Toxin Sac.description: A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.

Paralysis Sac.description: A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.

Omniplegia Sac.description: A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause paralysis.

Sleep Sac.description: A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing sleep.

Coma Sac.description: A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.

Flame Sac.description: A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with caution.

Inferno Sac.description: A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!

Conflagrant Sac.description: A monster organ filled with a highly explosive powder. Extremely dangerous!

Thunder Sac.description: A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high-voltage electricity.

Lightning Sac.description: A monster organ that can store electricity as strong as lightning. It rumbles like thunder.

Frost Sac.description: A monster organ that contains a sub-zero liquid. Handle with extreme care.

Freezer Sac.description: A monster organ with tremendous freezing power.

Cryo Sac.description: A monster organ that has fierce freezing properties. It can coat an area in ice in a flash.

Aqua Sac.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.

Torrent Sac.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.

Flood Sac.description: A monster organ designed to hold and preserve tremendous amounts of water.

Dash Extract.description: A mysterious substance that can be culled from certain monsters.

Pale Extract.description: Has the ability to amplify the effects of certain medicines.

Gargwa Feather.description: A big, beautiful feather plucked from a Gargwa. Often used as a fashion accessory.

Kelbi Horn.description: Infusions of powdered Kelbi Horn work wonders on tummyaches. It's a local secret!

Blue Kelbi Horn.description: An especially rare Kelbi Horn. Popular among traders.

Warm Pelt.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

High-quality Pelt.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

Prized Pelt.description: A pelt from a small animal. Used for many things, but mostly just regular clothes.

Rhenoplos Shell.description: A very strong shell, considering it comes such a small monster.

Rhenoplos Scalp.description: A sturdy part of the skill that yields, shall we say, dashing results?

Rhenoplos Bone.description: As strong as it is heavy, this Rhenoplos bone is well-suited for use in crafting armor.

Slagtoth Hide+.description: Firm, lustrous hide often cut into large slabs. Prized for its water-resistant properties.

Bnahabra Shell.description: Every bit as sturdy as wyvern armor in the hands of a clever craftsman.

Bnahabra Wing.description: Difficult to forge with -- the results vary depending on which surface you use.

Altaroth Jaw.description: These durable mouthparts are surprisingly difficult to carve loose.

Altaroth Stomach.description: A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.

Crushing Fang.description: The strongest fang of a fanged beast. It can pierce a monsters's shell as if it were paper.

Jaggi Scale.description: A scale carved from a Jaggi. Not very valuable, but beginners can't be choosers.

Jaggi Scale+.description: A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to produce hardier equipment.

Jaggi Hide.description: Commonly used in this region. It can be made into any number of things.

Bird Wyvern Fang.description: A fang similar in value to the foreign Velociprey's. Used to make bowgun ammo.

G.Jaggi Hide.description: Durable, elegantly patterned hide from a Great Jaggi. Befits its position as pack leader.

G.Jaggi Hide+.description: The rugged hide of a strong Great Jaggi. Fewer wounds means higher quality and value.

G.Jaggi Claw.description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Just like a Jaggi claw, only much, much larger.

G.Jaggi Claw+.description: A hook-shaped claw cut from a Great Jaggi. Well-Sharpened from countless battles.

King's Frill.description: Proof of who's boss among Jaggi -- and now proof you are on your way as a hunter.

Lagombi Pelt.description: A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One touch and you'll be hooked on its soft, fluffy fur.

Lagombi Pelt+.description: A quality white Lagombi pelt. Its glossy, frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.

Lagombi Fur.description: The very finest Lagombi fur, durable and yet surprisingly soft. A top-shelf item.

Lagombi Ear+.description: An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly-developed, it can become sharp as steel if polished.

Lagombi Auricle.description: A superior Lagombi ear with astonishing hearing capabilities. An exceptional crafting material.

Lagombi Plastron.description: A shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges are what allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.

Lagombi Plastron+.description: A robust Lagombi Plastron. Strong, sticky and thick, it's used to make superior equipment.

Monster Fluid.description: Sticky fluid that is often found in insects after they feast.

Monster Broth.description: A broth made from only the thickest of a monster's juices. Quite rich.

Monster Essence.description: A broth made from only the thickest, choicest parts of a monster's juices. Gross?

Black Pearl.description: The Hunting Fleet sometimes brings these back. The black glow fetches a high price.

Rathian Scale.description: A scale from a flying wyvern native to this area. Rathian mate with male Rathalos.

Rathian Scale+.description: A fine Rathian scale. It may not look special, but its hardness puts other scales to shame.

Rathian Shard.description: A particularly thick Rathian scale. Its large size proves its owner's advanced age.

Rathian Shell.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

Rathian Carapace.description: A sturdy Rathian carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathian shell.

Rathian Cortex.description: A Rathian shell heavier than a carapace. Used to reinforce parts of equipment.

Rathian Webbing.description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

Rathian Spike.description: Needle-like hair found on the Rathian's back and wings. They contain poison.

Rathian Spike+.description: As sharp as the keenest blade. It is longer and sturdier than other spikes.

Rathian Surspike.description: Only a few of those superior spikes grow on a Rathian. It is both sharp and highly toxic.

Rathian Plate.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

Rathian Ruby.description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathian. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

Rathian Mantle.description: A legendary Rathian scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

P.Rathian Scale+.description: A high-grade scale from a Pink Rathian. Chic hunters love the blend of strength and style.

P.Rathian Shard.description: A thick, shiny scale from a Pink Rathian. Rare is the artisan who has ever laid eyes on one.

P.Rathian Cortex.description: A hevy Pink Rathian cortex made up of a single beautiful plate. It commands top zenny when sold.

G.Rathian Shard.description: A thick Gold Rathian scale unlike anything seen before. Sunlight gives it an almost sacred glow.

G.Rathian Cortex.description: A cortex carved from a Gold Rathian. All who see it gasp at its intense glow.

G.Rath Surspike.description: A poisonous spike found on Gold Rathians in rare circumstances. It can pierce through anything.

Rathalos Scale.description: A Rathalos scale. Wyvern scales like this one and the harder shells are basic forging items.

Rathalos Scale+.description: An extraordinarily durable scale carved from the body of a Rathalos.

Rathalos Shard.description: A Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Its strength is a natural wonder.

Rathalos Shell.description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.

Rathalos Carapace.description: A rigid Rathalos carapace. Even harder than a normal Rathalos Shell.

Rathalos Cortex.description: A robust Rathalos shell that is harder and sturdier than a carapace.

Rathalos Webbing.description: Hard to forge with, but its thermal properties make it ideal for armor lining.

Rathalos Wing.description: A wing that has been removed. Skilled artisans can craft it into strong equipment.

Rathalos Fellwing.description: A top-grade Rathalos wing, removed in full. Such majesty befits the King of the Skies.

Rathalos Tail.description: The severed tail of a Rathalos. It has any number of uses.

Rathalos Lash.description: A top-grade Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are precious, and only used in select equipment.

Rathalos Plate.description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.

Rathalos Ruby.description: A rare gem formed inside a Rathalos. It seems almost too nice to forge with.

Rathalos Mantle.description: A legendary Rathalos scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

A.Rathalos Shard.description: An Azure Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. It boasts beauty and strength.

A.Rathalos Tail.description: The severed tail of an Azure Rathalos. It fetches a high price due to its rarity.

A.Rathalos Lash.description: A top-grade Azure Rathalos tail. Strong ones like this are prized by all and sold at high prices.

A.Rathalos Wing.description: A wing that has been removed. Excellent for forging both weapons and armor.

S.Rathalos Shard.description: A Silver Rathalos part made of several overlapping scales. Makes for a nice silver accessory.

S.Rath Cortex.description: A heavy Silver Rathalos cortex. This legendary item shines like moonlight, even in darkness.

Rath Marrow.description: Recent advances allow this marrow to be extracted. It ignites on air contact.

Rath Medulla.description: Recent advances allow this red hot organ to be removed, but it's hard to forge with.

Diablos Cortex.description: The rigid cortex of a Diablos, both harder and sturdier than its carapace.

Diablos Chine.description: Tough Diablos backplate, strengthened by burning sands. An ideal material for armor.

Diablos Hardhorn.description: An especially elegant Diablos horn with almost perfect shape. An extremely rare material.

B.Diablos Cortex.description: A heavy Black Diablos cortex. Its weight reveals its overwhelming density and strength.

B.Diablos Chine.description: Finely honed Black Diablos backplate. Best described as black, hard, and heavy.

Zinogre Carapace.description: The teal carapace of a Zinogre. Its magnificence reveals the futility of facing the monarch.

Zinogre Cortex.description: The teal cortex of a Zinogre. The monarch's armor crushes wills with its immense power.

Zinogre Horn+.description: A pointed Zinogre horn. When carved, it can be used to grant equipment incomparable power.

Zinogre Hardhorn.description: A mighty Zinogre horn. None can sand before its sky-shattering, awe-inspiring power.

Zinogre Claw+.description: A sharp, high voltage Zinogre claw. Its electrified attacks are truly brutal.

Zinogre Tail.description: The plate-covered tail of a Zinogre. It wields deadly force when swung.

Zinogre Lash.description: A superior Zinogre tail that wields incomparable destructive power.

Zinogre Shocker+.description: A Zinogre shell that stores and releases electricity. Grants a thunder god's power to gear.

Zinogre Jasper.description: A rare gem occasionally produced inside a Zinogre's body. The monarch's power swells within.

S.Zinogre Lash.description: A Stygian Zinogre's terrifyingly strong tail. Said to be able to slice through solid steel.

Dracophage Bug.description: Dragonfell Berry-loving bugs that store up Dragon energy. A Stygian Zinogre's power source

Brach Carapace.description: A hard Brachydios carapace. Glossy like obsidian, it adds a refined beauty to crafted gear.

Brach Cortex.description: The thick cortex of a Brachydios. Its stoic beauty adds strength and dignity to equipment.

Brach Ebonshell.description: An obsidian Brachydios brace. Makes especially strong armor, perhaps due to the slime mold.

Brach Ebonshell+.description: A premium Brachydios brace. The slime coating may contain weird bacteria, so be careful.

Brach Scalp.description: The large, protruding scalp of a Brachydios, covered in an explosive green substance.

Brach Scalp+.description: A hard and sharp scalp piece from a fierce Brachydios. Even more explosive than usual.

Mystery Slime.description: The explosive green substance found on Brachydios monsters. Handle with extreme care.

Glowing Slime.description: Highly explosive green slime found on a fierce Brachydios. Handle with extreme care.

Brach Pounder.description: A Brachydios arm that buried countless foolhardy hunters. It's covered in green slime.

Brach Pounder+.description: The arm of an especially angry Brachydios. Strong and heavy, as if made of iron.

Brach Pallium.description: A legendary Brachydios shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

Deviljho Scale.description: A greenish-black Deviljho scale. It's not often sold, as rumors claim it brings it misfortune.

Deviljho Shard.description: A heavy, high-quality Deviljho scale. Rumored to bring bad luck, but actually an excellent material.

Deviljho Hide.description: Black hide that is oddly slimy and difficult to forge with.

Deviljho Talon.description: A dangerously sharp, hooked talon. Inexperienced crafters risk serious injury.

Deviljho Ripper.description: An incredibly sharp, rigid talon. Even experienced handlers can be injured if not careful.

Deviljho Scalp.description: Removing this part of a Deviljho's skull releases an unimaginably putrid odor.

Deviljho Tail.description: A masive tail resembling a fin. Some folks are out to collect these exclusively.

Deviljho Flail.description: A large slab of a Deviljho's leech-like tail. Even so-called experts are shocked by it.

Deviljho Saliva.description: The symbol of a Deviljho's insatiable appetite. The strong acid corrodes all it touches.

Black Blood.description: Dark black blood characteristic of a Deviljho. It feels like it could jump up and attack at any time.

Vile Fang.description: A massive, overgrown fang that can chomp through anything. Filled with pure evil.

Deviljho Gem.description: A precious gem said to contain a Deviljho's might. Used in shady rituals.

Deviljho Crook.description: An unsettling scale that became warped as it absorbed the malice of the Deviljho's various prey.

Earth Dragongem.description: One of the tougher materials to get from a Jhen Mohran, and that's saying something.

Arzuros Shell.description: A shell piece from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.

Arzuros Pelt.description: A pelt carved from an Arzuros. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.

Spongy Hide.description: Uncannily elastic hide that retains water quite well.

Vivid Feather.description: A superbly colored Qurupeo feather. Nothing less than a natural work of art.

Strange Beak.description: An oddly shaped beak. It's pleasant enough.

Barroth Shell.description: A Barroth's shell -- more often than not covered in mud, but strong either way.

Barroth Scalp.description: This durable part of the skull is also the hardest to remove.

Nibelsnarf Hide.description: Hide from a Nibelsnarf. Many are surprised by its bright colors, in contrast to the outer shell.

Vivid Fluid.description: A fluid which helps retain water in a Nibelsnarf and allows the beast to thrive in the desert.

Uragaan Marrow.description: Hard-to-obtain bone marrow used for special crafts as well as medicinal purposes.

Uragaan Scute.description: Even more heat resistant than the Shell, this is said to protect sensitive organs.

Duramboros Horn.description: The horn of a Duramboros. Wider than a man's chest；all who see it are rendered speechless.

Diablos Shell.description: This shell piece is dense, as one knock will tell you, and heavier than it looks.

Majestic Horn.description: A twisted Diablos horn in great shape. Use it to make more powerful weapons.

Gobul Hide+.description: Fine skin from a Gobul. Said to rejuvenate the skin, and quite popular with the ladies.

Gobul Spike+.description: A high-quality barb from a Gobul. Only stroner monsters have such well-shaped spikes.

Amber Tusks+.description: Amber tusks sharpened by countless kills. They can smash through gigantic ice blocks.

Barioth Pelt+.description: A high-quality white pelt with a lovely texture. Nobles use it as a symbol of authority.

Shell Shocker+.description: A superior shell found only on certain Lagiacrus. Its structure permits greater electric output.

Agnaktor Fin+.description: An Agnaktor fin with an elegant dappled pattern. Aparently a popular item with collectors.

Ceadeus Hide.description: Even for monster skin, this is remarkably solid. Takes time and effort to craft.

Crooked Horn.description: A giant horn that was formed over ages. It evinces all weight of history.

Luminous Organ.description: Who knows why this organ glows, but it seems to hold incredible power.

Alatreon Plate.description: This particular Alatreon scale grows in backwards. It is as sharp as a blade.

Alatreon Webbing.description: At times this looks like a dark abyss； at others, like the coming of first light.

Qurupeco Shard.description: A strong scale concealed by vivid plumage, grown to full maturity over many years.

Lustrous Feather.description: A vivid feather with an elegant luster. Qurupeco with these only live in certain regions.

Gobul Piel.description: Thick skin from a Gobul. Too rubbery for eating, but perfect for crafting equipment.

Gobul Surspike.description: An unusual barb from a Gobul. Only the most formidable of the breed have such precious spikes.

Arzuros Cortex.description: A superior Arzuros cortext. This highly-developed shell is a huge thorn in all hunters' sides.

Dazzling Fluid.description: A sparkling fluid with impressive water-retention ability. Improves performance and style.

Barroth Cortex.description: A Barroth's cortex. Years worth of mud have hardened it beyond all measure.

Barroth Crown.description: The heavy scalp of a formidable Barroth. As hard to remove as it is durable.

Volvidon Cortex.description: A heavy Volvidon cortext. Difficult to forge with, but can produce genuinely powerful gear.

Agnaktor Cortex.description: The rigid cortex of an Agnaktor. Highly heat-resistant, it produces bright red items when forged.

J.Barroth Cortex.description: The solid, ice-covered cortex of a Jade Barroth. The frosty coating is surprisngly strong.

Durambolite.description: A legendary gem rarely produced inside a Duramboros's body. Elegant, though gloomy.

Uragaan Cortex.description: An especially hard Uragaan cortex. Crafting with it can be a trying task, to say the least.

Uragaan Pallium.description: A legendary Uragaan shell. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

Nargacuga Mantle.description: A legendary Nargacuga scale. Those who craft it are said to rule the earth and seize the sky.

Lagiacrus Shard.description: The ultimate specimen of Lagiacrus Scale. Special skills are required to craft with it.

Deathly Shocker.description: A thick shell found on a select few Lagiacrus. It releases huge bolts of electricity.

Lagiacrus Mantle.description: A valuable azure scale found on select Lagiacrus. Said to greatly boost equipment performance.

I.Lagi D-Shocker.description: A thick shell seen only rarely on Ivory Lagiacrus. It can produce a veritable rain of thunderbolts.

I.Lagi Hardhorn.description: A fine horn from an Ivory Lagiacrus. Beloved by the rich for its flawless elegance.

S.Uragaan Scute+.description: A highly heat-resistant Steel Uragaan scute. Its rigidity makes it hard to use in forging.

Ceadeus Scale.description: Almost too large to be called a scale. Not as hard as you might think.

Deep Dragongem.description: One of the hardest materials to reap from a Ceadeus. Its center is a bottomless void.

Mohran Rockskin.description: A heavy shell piece taken from a Jhen Mohran. It surpasses even steel in strength.

Mohran Allbrace.description: A thick, high quality brace from a Jhen Mohran. Easy craftable with the right amount of force.

Deific Fang.description: A beautiful fang with a divine aura. Its shape and color best other Jhen Mohran fangs.

Cloudy Moonshard.description: The moon-like bladewing of a Lucent Nargacuga. He who crafts it controls the night.

Alatreon Mantle.description: The mantle of an Alatreon is the stuff of legend, containing traces of every element within.

A.Lagi D-Shocker.description: A thick shell from an Abyssal Lagiacrus's back. Turns the sea itself into an electrified weapon.

A.Lagi Dynamo.description: An unknown Abyssal Lagiacrus organ. Rumored to be the source of the monster's electricity.

Miralis Scale.description: A fiery black scale from a Dire Miralis. Also called the burning flower

Miralis Smelter.description: A burning hot core from a Dire Miralis's hips. A magma-like substance swirls inside it.

Dire Dragongem.description: A legendary gem expelled from the body of a Dire Miralis. It formed from crystallized magma.

Rustshard.description: A hunk of rock? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

Ancient Shard.description: A fossil? No, it seems to be metal... With a little polish, it could be more.

Rusted Fragment.description: A uniquely shaped metal fragment covered in rust. It looks like it could be used for something..

Map.description: A map of the hunting ground.

First-aid Med.description: Restores a tiny bit of Health. It does a body... sort of good!

Ration.description: Slightly boosts current/max Stamina. Most hunters agree: it's gross.

Portable Spit.description: A Guild-provided BBQ Spit useful for novice hunters.

Mini Whetstone.description: A portable Whetstone you can use to restore Sharpness to weapons.

EZ Shock Trap.description: Immobilizes a target for easy capture.

EZ Flash Bomb.description: A grenade-like bomb that flashes brightly on impact.

EZ Barrel Bomb L.description: A powered-up Barrel Bomb L (as potent as a B. Bomb L+). OK underwater.

Ballista Ammo.description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun.

Ballista Binder.description: Ammunition for a large mounted Bowgun. Keep giants from moving!

Cannon Ammo.description: Special ammunition for an anti-dragon cannon. Not fun to lug around.

Anti-dragon Bomb.description: A small time bomb that sticks to targets.

Torch.description: Use this to light up dark places and stave off certain monsters.

Paw Pass Ticket.description: Deliver to end the Quest. Maybe the Felynes will take you home...

Unique Mushroom.description: A pinky-sized mushroom valued for its unusual aroma.

Choice Mushroom.description: The perfect shape and aroma. Even better than a Unique Mushroom.

Ripened Mushroom.description: A unique Mushroom made more unique by maturing its aroma and flavor.

Goldenfish.description: A rare fish made of solid gold. Sell it for a tidy sum.

Royal Rhino.description: A beetle with a jewel-like gleam. Prized by bug fans of all ages.

Crystal Bone.description: A unique bone prized in the village for reasons unknown.

Bloodstone.description: Is this crimson stone the relic of some ancient beast?

Monster Guts.description: Monster innards galore. A prized delicacy.

Popo Tongue.description: Popo Tongue are popular, healthy, and fun to eat.

Wyvern Egg.description: An egg taken from a flying wyvern's nest. Very fragile, so handle with care.

Herbivore Egg.description: An egg stolen from an herbivore's nest. It looks pretty tasty.

Powderstone.description: A rock that explodes with even the slightest jolt. Careful!

Wyvern Tear.description: Mysterious tears wept only on special occasions.

Pinnacle Coin.description: A glorious coin given only to unquestioned Masters of Hunting. Beyond priceless.

Hunter King Coin.description: A silver coin given only to True Hunters. Its gleam is a symbol of your glory.

Beast Coin.description: An award granted for defeating a fanged beast in the Arena. A sharp fang is carved on it.

Flying Coin.description: An award granted for defeating a flying wyvern in the Arena. Proof one challenged the skies.

Voucher.description: Redeem this for a special meal with stronger effects than usual.

Gourmet Voucher.description: Exchange this for a kingly meal. Both its flavor and effects are top notch.

Commendation.description: A ticket awarded for a display of bravery. Collect enough and it might pay off.

Conqueror's Seal.description: Proof you have overcome countless trials, and a true badge of honor.

Pawprint Stamp.description: Lynain paper currency, stamped with a pawprint. The letters written on it are unfamiliar.

VE Ticket.description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

VE Deluxe Ticket.description: A ticket awarded in recognition of contributions to the Guild. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

VE Bronze Ticket.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. Trade it with the Veggie Elder.

VE Silver Ticket.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer a rare trade...

VE Cosmic Ticket.description: A ticket awarded for hunting with friends. The Veggie Elder may offer an amazing trade...

Steel Egg.description: A egg of glittering steel. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

Silver Egg.description: A egg of glittering silver. Very valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

Golden Egg.description: An egg of glittering gold. Insanely valuable and rare, but of no use to a hunter.

Aquaglow Jewel.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

Sunspire Jewel.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations.

Bloodrun Jewel.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A shame that these are so high-end.

Lazurite Jewel.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. This one doesn't come along often.

Adamant Orb.description: An indispensible item used in Decorations. A rare orb that houses immense power.
